<subSubSection box="[151,769,764,789]" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,764,933]" box="[151,769,764,789]" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">
25. Recognize a monospecific 
<emphasis box="[494,615,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Spodiornis</emphasis>
Sclater, 1866
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="342" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,764,933]" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">
(type = 
<emphasis box="[862,1073,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Spodiornis jardinii</emphasis>
Sclater, 1866, a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Tschudi, 1844" authorityName="Tschudi" authorityYear="1844" box="[184,563,799,824]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Phrygilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rusticus">
<emphasis box="[184,391,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Phrygilus rusticus</emphasis>
Tschudi, 1844
</taxonomicName>
, currently 
<taxonomicName box="[688,903,799,824]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Haplospiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rustica">
<emphasis box="[688,903,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Haplospiza rustica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), for 
<taxonomicName box="[971,1187,799,824]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Haplospiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rustica">
<emphasis box="[971,1187,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Haplospiza rustica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1204,1275,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[481,1098,203,1904]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Maximum clade credibility tree from the Bayesian analyses of Burns et al. (2014). Subfamily Diglossinae shown. Labeling and format as in Fig. 1." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/266315/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="342" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,764,933]" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">
Because the name 
<emphasis box="[222,343,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Spodiornis</emphasis>
is masculine in gender and 
<taxonomicName box="[679,807,836,861]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Haplospiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[679,807,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Haplospiza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is feminine, the ending of adjectival specific epithets changes to agree: 
<taxonomicName box="[352,465,872,895]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Haplospiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rustica">
<emphasis box="[352,465,872,895]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">H. rustica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
becomes 
<taxonomicName box="[577,694,872,896]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Phrygilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rusticus">
<emphasis box="[577,694,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">S. rusticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[708,842,872,895]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">
H. r. 
<taxonomicName box="[764,842,872,895]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Haplospiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rustica">rustica</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
becomes 
<emphasis box="[954,1093,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">
S. r. 
<taxonomicName box="[1004,1093,872,895]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Phrygilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rusticus">rusticus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<emphasis box="[1154,1288,872,895]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">H. r. arcana</emphasis>
(Wetmore &amp; Phelps, 1949) becomes 
<emphasis box="[417,556,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">S. r. arcanus</emphasis>
(the last as originally described).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
